quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  22,26,"When We settled for Abraham the site of the House [saying], Do not ascribe any partners to Me, and purify My House for those who circle around it, and those who stand [in it for prayer], and those who bow and prostrate themselves"
  22,27,"And proclaim the Hajj to all the people: they will come to you on foot and on lean camels, coming from distant places"
  22,28,"that they may witness the benefits for them, and mention Allah’s Name during the known days over the livestock He has provided them. So eat thereof and feed the destitute and the needy"
  22,29,"Then let them do away with their untidiness, fulfill their vows, and circle around the Ancient House"
  22,30,"That, and whoever venerates the sacraments of Allah, that is better for him with his Lord. You are permitted [animals of] grazing livestock except for what will be recited to you. So avoid the abomination of idols, and avoid false speech"
  22,31,"as persons having pure faith in Allah, not ascribing partners to Him. Whoever ascribes partners to Allah is as though he had fallen from a height, then [his corpse] is devoured by vultures, or [his remains are] blown away by the wind far and wide"
  22,32,That. And whoever venerates the sacraments of Allah—indeed that arises from the Godwariness of hearts
  22,33,You may benefit from them until a specified time. Then their place of sacrifice is by the Ancient House